						<summary>

						<p>Refers to the gift of the village of <hi rend="bold">Mulkalapāḍu</hi> in the province of <hi rend="bold">Ojīvi</hi> to god Anantīśvara. The donor's name is lost. Refers to the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva (Vikramāditya VI)</hi> who was ruling at <hi rend="bold">Kalyāṇapura.</hi></p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

